This paper is about efficiently training linear models with elastic net regularization, which is a common technique in machine learning. The paper discusses algorithms for updating the weights of the model using stochastic gradient descent and forward backward splitting, which are commonly used optimization techniques in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
